  "diffSummary": "Reconciliation of the message-cache feature merged in f343624 (its code shipped but the harness tracking was never completed). The store/ layer (src-tauri/src/store/db.rs) persists threads/messages/attachments on the bundled SQLite store: save_message upserts the thread and inserts the message deduped by (account_id, msg_id), bumping unread only for distinct inbound messages; save_attachment stores attachment metadata; load_threads/load_recent_messages return ordered history; clear_unread resets a thread. The command/ layer persists incoming messages on the listener bridge (persist_incoming) and outgoing messages on send, exposes load_history + mark_thread_read, and the frontend (src/lib/session.svelte.ts) hydrates conversations + per-thread messages from load_history at login/restore. types/stored.rs carries the StoredThread/StoredMessage/History DTOs (camelCase, no secrets). This reconciliation adds the previously-missing offline restart smoke (message_cache_roundtrip): it saves an inbound + outbound + group message, drops the Db (simulating app shutdown / connection close), reopens the SAME SQLite file (relaunch), and asserts all threads + messages are restored with no realtime event — which is exactly the durability boundary the feature claims.",
  "changedFiles": [
    "src-tauri/src/store/db.rs"
  ],
